Course

public Course(java.lang.String name,
              float creditpoints,
              java.lang.String semester,
              int year)
Course class constructor, sets course grade to zero. If you want to create an unfinished course, use this constructor.

Parameters:
name - Course name.
creditpoints - Credit points awarded for the course.
semester - The semester during which the course is completed (or during which an unfinished course is started).
year - The year during which the course is completed (or during which an unfinished course is started).

Parameters:
name - Course name.
creditpoints - Credit points awarded for the Course.
semester - The semester during which this Course is completed (or during which an unfinished Course is started).
year - The year during which this Course is completed (or during which an unfinished Course is started).
grade - The grade awarded for this Course. Integer in range [0,5].
